\f1\b \cf0 FLOWARTS.NET AND THE CURATING OF "GLOBAL" TAGS/CATEGORIES/LAYERS
\b0 \
Flowarts.net will develop the core global taxonomy. This will be the default view on the flowarts.net site. \
\
Types of events include:\
-Individuals\
-Teachers\
-Lessons\
-Training spaces\
-Shops\
-Spin-jams\
-Flow Specific Festivals (like a hooping festival)\
-Flow Friendly Festivals (like Burning Man or certain electronic music festivals) \
-Great places to play\
\
Types of tags include:\
-Type of Flow Art\
--Poi\
--Staffs\
--Hoop\
--Flow-wand\
-Individuals\
--Has permission to tag "international"\
--Willing to teach\
--Wants to make new flow-arts friends\
-Other tags?\
\
Thus a user could look for other individuals who play with poi in their area. Or poi lessons within their province. Etc. \
\
Some layers may need a degree of permissions. I.e. users may have to apply for permission to tag events as International (criteria to be developed later). If they abuse this privilege their permission will be revoked. In time there will be trusted users in each region. The map itself will show people who their local trusted user is. So if they want to tag an event international, they will be directed to communicate with the local liaison. \
\
Note: We see no need for a thumbs-up / thumbs-down approach. If the map is well designed people will rarely see events that are not relevant to them. Also, under what circumstance would somebody give a thumbs-down to an event? \
\
