\f0\b \cf0 HOST SITES: FLOWMAP EXPRESSIONS
\b0 \
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural

\f1 \cf0 A primary feature is the ability of each website owner to customize the default displays of the flowmap to meet the values and speciality of their website. There are three levels to this, which may appear as three boxes with toggles:\
\
BOX #1: The host-site default layers and views: This is the host website's selection of elements to display on the map. The host also chooses which are toggled on and off by default. I.e. Playpoi.com may wish to by default show an international map of all Playpoi and friends-of-playpoi international events. A site for a Boston-based poi teacher may just default to a view of Boston showing where their lessons happen. \
\
BOX #2: Global Views: These are the global elements set by Flowarts.net. This will in itself be the default view when one visits the Flowmap on Flowarts.net. \
\
BOX #3: Mandatory links, etc. \
This may include:\
-A link back to flowarts.net\
-A link to a listing of all the websites displaying the flow-map
\f0\b \
