\b OTHER PROBLEMS TO SOLVE:\

\b0 \
For repeating events, such as weekly spin-jams, how can we keep them current? Can we set a maximum of six months of repeating? And then the poster gets a message saying they have to extend the event? \
\
-What are other ways people may abuse the system? \
\
\
\

\b SOME IDEAS ABOUT HOW PEOPLE WILL USE THE MAPS:
\b0 \
Say I'm trying to promote myself as a poi teacher. Great! I can put up my own website, embed the map, and make the default view display my events! But if I want those events to show on playpoi's default view, then of course I need to meet somebody from Playpoi and show them what a great teacher I am.\
\
There will be bad performers and bad teachers listing themselves. This is where the tags are important. It will hopefully be clear to users that when they toggle "all poi teachers" from the global box, it shows all poi teachers, regardless of their reputation. Thus users will often first look to "host site recommended teachers" or another filter/tag to help them find quality. \
\
\
\

\b OTHER THOUGHTS
\b0 \
As a site owner I can create as many tags and even custom categories as I wish, and order/stack them as I see fit. But of course if I make this complicated I'm guaranteeing that they will only be displaying on my own website!\
\
I may also want to display custom layers created by other users. For instance, I may want to display a layer showing the venues of a performance of a performance troupe I like. Thus I just add "all performances tagged suchandsuch" to the Playpoi default view. \
\
An important issue: When are layers toggled on/off by the viewer and which layers automatically toggle on/off depending on view zoom? Darren wrote: "
\f2\fs26 Depending on the zoom level, pins could be "clustered" to display a single pin with a number. Clicking on it would expand the cluster and redraw with all of the pins/points within displayed." 
\f1\fs24 \
\
It will need to be clear to users that global events will appear on other instances of the flowmap (once toggled or zoomed in, etc.), but custom events/tags will only show up when/if other sites choose. \
\
We will need a way to submit new layers/tags to flowarts.net for consideration to be upgraded to global. \
